Sentencas: The continuing development of new materials suitable for solid oxide fuel cells operating at about 650-800 degreesC is of great interest in recent days.
Titulo: Microstructure and electrical conductivity of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 prepared by combustion synthesis routes

Sentencas: The present investigation deals with the development of a perovskite composition-LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 (LNF)-prepared following two combustion synthesis routes: citrate-gel (LNC) and urea (LNU).
Titulo: Microstructure and electrical conductivity of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 prepared by combustion synthesis routes

Sentencas: The powders were sintered over a wide temperature range (900-1400 degreesC) and sintering behavior for LNC and LNU was compared.
Titulo: Microstructure and electrical conductivity of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 prepared by combustion synthesis routes

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient (TEC), electrical and microstructural characteristics of LNF was thoroughly investigated.
Titulo: Microstructure and electrical conductivity of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 prepared by combustion synthesis routes

Sentencas: Electrical conductivities were found to be one and a half times higher than that of most commonly used cathode material, La(Sr)MnO3.
Titulo: Microstructure and electrical conductivity of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 prepared by combustion synthesis routes

Sentencas: Moreover, the TEC value of LNF was found to be approximate to11.4 x 10(-6) K-1 at 800 degreesC.
Titulo: Microstructure and electrical conductivity of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 prepared by combustion synthesis routes

Sentencas: The study opens up a possibility of using LNF as a promising cell component for SOFC.
Titulo: Microstructure and electrical conductivity of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 prepared by combustion synthesis routes
